# RoundLabs — environment variables (EXAMPLE). Copy to .env.local for dev.
# NEVER commit real secrets. Only VITE_-prefixed vars reach the browser, and the
# browser must only ever see the ENDPOINT URL — never a provider API key.

# Serverless endpoint that performs video analysis. When unset, the app uses the
# honest manual fallback (never claims "AI analyzed").
VITE_VIDEO_ANALYSIS_ENDPOINT=

# GitHub Pages base path. "/" for local/dev and user/org pages; "/<repo>/" for a
# project page. Set as a GitHub Actions *variable* (not a secret) at build time.
# VITE_BASE=/roundlabs/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SERVER-SIDE ONLY (do NOT prefix with VITE_, do NOT expose to the client).
# These live in the serverless function's environment, never in this frontend.
# PROVIDER_API_KEY=
# PROVIDER_MODEL=
